'''Obed Gómez Vargas''' (born August 5, 2005) is a professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[central midfielder]] for {{Spanish football updater|Atlético Madrid}} club [[Atlético Madrid]]. Born in the United States, he represents the [[Mexico national football team|Mexico national team]].<ref name="prosoccerwire.usatoday.com">{{Cite web|url=https://prosoccerwire.usatoday.com/2024/06/12/obed-vargas-switches-from-usmnt-to-mexico/|title=USMNT loses highly rated Sounders midfielder Vargas to Mexico|date=June 12, 2024}}</ref>

Vargas joined the academy of [[Seattle Sounders FC]] in [[Major League Soccer]] (MLS) and signed a contract for their reserve team, [[Tacoma Defiance]], in 2021. He made his MLS debut that same year at the age of 15 years old and later became a regular starter for the Sounders, where he played for five seasons. In 2026, he joined Spanish side Atlético Madrid.

== Youth career ==
Born in [[Anchorage, Alaska]], Vargas began his career with Cook Inlet Soccer Club; he also traveled to [[Arizona]] to play in youth tournaments where he was later scouted.<ref name="ADN">{{cite news |last=Bragg |first=Beth |date=July 24, 2021 |title=15-year-old Anchorage boy starts for Seattle Sounders to make Major League Soccer history |url=https://www.adn.com/sports/2021/07/23/15-year-old-anchorage-boy-starts-for-seattle-sounders-to-make-major-league-soccer-history/ |work=[[Anchorage Daily News]] |accessdate=December 29, 2021}}</ref><ref name="MLS-2024">{{cite news |last=Deossa |first=Andy |date=July 17, 2024 |title=Obed Vargas blossoms with Seattle Sounders: The Pathway |url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/news/obed-vargas-blossoms-with-seattle-sounders-the-pathway |work=MLSsoccer.com |accessdate=February 6, 2026}}</ref> He moved to [[Washington (state)|Washington]] and joined the youth academy for [[Major League Soccer]] club [[Seattle Sounders FC]] at the age of 14.<ref name="MLS-2024" />

==Club career==

===Seattle Sounders FC===

Vargas played in the academy of Seattle Sounders FC for two seasons before signing a professional contract with Sounders FC reserve side [[Tacoma Defiance]] on May 7, 2021.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Foss |first1=Tim |title=Defiance add two Academy products |url=https://www.sounderatheart.com/thefuture/2021/5/7/22425632/juan-alvarez-obed-vargas-sign-tacoma-defiance |access-date=May 10, 2021 |work=Sounder at Heart |date=May 7, 2021 |archive-date=March 26, 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220326021924/https://www.sounderatheart.com/thefuture/2021/5/7/22425632/juan-alvarez-obed-vargas-sign-tacoma-defiance |url-status=dead }}</ref> Two days later, he made his senior debut for Tacoma Defiance in the [[USL Championship]] against [[LA Galaxy II]]. Vargas started and played 66 minutes as the match ended in a 1–1 draw.<ref>{{cite web |title=LA Galaxy II 1–1 Tacoma Defiance |url=https://us.soccerway.com/matches/2021/05/10/united-states/mls-reserve-league/la-galaxy-ii/seattle-sounders-ii/3484935/ |website=Soccerway}}</ref>

He made his MLS debut for Seattle on July 22, 2021, as one of several Tacoma Defiance players called up to the Sounders for a match against [[Austin FC]] to replace injured players. At 15 years and 351 days old, Vargas was the third-youngest player in MLS history.<ref name="ADN"/> He signed a formal [[Homegrown Player Rule (Major League Soccer)|Homegrown Player]] contract with the Sounders in December and became a starter for the team in the first matches of the 2022 season, playing in two [[2022 CONCACAF Champions League|CONCACAF Champions League]] fixtures. Head coach [[Brian Schmetzer]] described Vargas' play style as similar to that of [[Cristian Roldan]]'s rookie season, adding he was "going to be a tremendous player for our club".<ref name="Times-Veteran">{{cite news |last=Evans |first=Jayda |date=March 10, 2022 |title=16-year-old Obed Vargas playing like a veteran already with Sounders |url=https://www.seattletimes.com/sports/sounders/16-year-old-obed-vargas-playing-like-a-veteran-already-with-sounders/ |work=[[The Seattle Times]] |accessdate=March 12, 2022}}</ref> He was an early substitute in the second leg of the [[2022 CONCACAF Champions League final]], which the Sounders won 3–0 at home.<ref>{{cite magazine |last=Creditor |first=Avi |date=May 4, 2022 |title=Seattle Ends MLS's CCL Futility, Routs Pumas to Win Concacaf's Title |url=https://www.si.com/soccer/2022/05/05/seattle-sounders-pumas-unam-ccl-final-video-highlights |magazine=[[Sports Illustrated]] |accessdate=May 4, 2024}}</ref>

Vargas made 13 appearances through late June, when a stress facture in his back prevented him from continuing with the team. He was also unable to join the under-20 national team in the [[2022 CONCACAF U-20 Championship|CONCACAF U-20 Championship]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Liljenwall |first=Ari |date=June 24, 2022 |title=Seattle Sounders midfielder Obed Vargas sidelined "multiple weeks" with back injury |url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/news/seattle-sounders-midfielder-obed-vargas-sidelined-multiple-weeks-with-back-injur |work=MLSsoccer.com |accessdate=May 4, 2024}}</ref> Vargas returned for the 2023 season but played in few matches, including only 24 minutes in the [[2023 MLS Cup playoffs|MLS Cup playoffs]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Oshan |first=Jeremiah |date=February 15, 2024 |title=Obed Vargas willing to bide time after disappointing end to 2023 |url=https://www.sounderatheart.com/2024/02/obed-vargas-preseason/ |work=Sounder At Heart |accessdate=May 4, 2024}}</ref> He regained the starting position in midfield for the 2024 season and scored his first career MLS goal on April 30, 2024, against the [[Philadelphia Union]], in a match that was originally started a month earlier but postponed due to heavy rain.<ref>{{cite news |last=Evans |first=Jayda |date=April 30, 2024 |title=Raul Ruidiaz's brace leads Sounders over Union in completion of suspended game |url=https://www.seattletimes.com/sports/sounders/raul-ruidiazs-brace-leads-sounders-over-union-in-completion-of-suspended-game/ |work=The Seattle Times |accessdate=May 4, 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Evans |first=Jayda |date=May 11, 2024 |title=Sounders' Obed Vargas backing up first MLS goal with sharp play |url=https://www.seattletimes.com/sports/sounders/sounders-obed-vargas-backing-up-first-mls-goal-with-sharp-play/ |work=The Seattle Times |accessdate=February 6, 2026}}</ref> Vargas played over 3,000 minutes for the Sounders in the 2024 season and was ranked seventh in the MLS 22 Under 22 list at the end of the regular season.<ref>{{cite press release |date=October 9, 2024 |title=Obed Vargas selected for 22 Under 22 presented by Bodyarmour |url=https://www.soundersfc.com/news/obed-vargas-selected-for-22-under-22-presented-by-bodyarmour |publisher=Seattle Sounders FC |accessdate=February 6, 2026}}</ref> He was suspended for the first match of the [[2024 MLS Cup playoffs|2024 playoffs]] after receiving two [[yellow card (sports)|yellow card]] in a match against the [[Portland Timbers]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Evans |first=Jayda |date=October 31, 2024 |title=Jordan Morris' injury status, Vargas back and players fined |url=https://www.seattletimes.com/sports/sounders/jordan-morris-injury-status-vargas-back-and-players-fined-sounders-notebook/ |work=The Seattle Times |accessdate=February 6, 2026}}</ref>

During the [[2025 Seattle Sounders FC season|2025 regular season]], Vargas started in 26 matches and finished second on the team in minutes played.<ref name="Times-YPOTY">{{cite news |last=Evans |first=Jayda |date=October 23, 2025 |title=Sounders' Obed Vargas named finalist for MLS Young Player of the Year |url=https://www.seattletimes.com/sports/sounders/sounders-obed-vargas-named-finalist-for-mls-young-player-of-the-year/ |work=The Seattle Times |accessdate=February 6, 2026}}</ref> He was a starter for Seattle's three matches in the [[2025 FIFA Club World Cup]] group stage and played for the team's entire [[2025 Leagues Cup]] run, where the Sounders won the title.<ref name="Times-Atletico"/> Vargas was named to the roster for the [[2025 MLS All-Star Game]] and played in the match; he was also ranked first in the 2025 MLS 22 Under 22 list.<ref>{{cite news |date=February 2, 2026 |title=Seattle Sounders to Atlético Madrid: Obed Vargas' 10 biggest MLS moments |url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/news/seattle-sounders-to-atletico-madrid-obed-vargas-10-biggest-mls-moments |work=MLSsoccer.com |accessdate=February 6, 2026}}</ref> Vargas was also a finalist for the 2025 [[MLS Young Player of the Year Award]].<ref name="Times-YPOTY"/> In his five seasons with the Sounders, Vargas scored 8 goals in 130 appearances across all competitions.<ref name="Times-Atletico"/>

===Atlético Madrid===

On February 2, 2026, [[La Liga]] club [[Atlético Madrid]] announced the signing of Vargas on a four-and-a-half-year contract in the closing hours of the [[transfer window]].<ref name="Times-Atletico"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://en.atleticodemadrid.com/noticias/welcome-obed-vargas|title=Welcome, Obed Vargas!|publisher=Atlético Madrid|date=February 2, 2026|accessdate=February 2, 2026}}</ref> He had rejected an earlier offer from [[Club América]] of [[Liga MX]] to pursue a career in the European leagues.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Becherano |first1=Lizzy |last2=Carlisle |first2=Jeff |date=February 2, 2026 |title=Seattle Sounders midfielder Obed Vargas joins Atlético Madrid |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/47809097/seattle-sounders-midfielder-obed-vardgas-joins-atletico-madrid |publisher=ESPN |accessdate=February 5, 2026}}</ref> Vargas previously stated that Atlético Madrid had been his favorite team as a child; he also played against them in the 2025 FIFA Club World Cup.<ref name="Times-Atletico">{{cite news |last=Vesely |first=Sophia |date=February 2, 2026 |title=Sounders transfer star midfielder Obed Vargas to La Liga's Atletico Madrid |url=https://www.seattletimes.com/sports/sounders/sounders-transfer-star-midfielder-obed-vargas-to-la-ligas-atletico-madrid/ |work=The Seattle Times |accessdate=February 5, 2026}}</ref> He made his debut for Atlético as a substitute in the 79th minute of a [[2025–26 Copa del Rey|Copa del Rey]] quarterfinal match against [[Real Betis]].<ref>{{cite news |date=February 5, 2026 |title=¿Cómo fue el debut de Obed Vargas con el Atlético de Madrid? |language=Spanish |trans-title=How was Obed Vargas' debut with Atlético Madrid? |url=https://espndeportes.espn.com/futbol/espana/nota/_/id/16275575/obed-vargas-debut-atletico-madrid-copa-rey-cuartos-final-betis |publisher=ESPN Deportes |accessdate=February 6, 2026}}</ref> He recorded his first goal contribution for Atlético Madrid on May 2nd 2026, providing an assist in a 2-0 victory over [[Valencia]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Obed Vargas shines with assist in Atlético Madrid’s win over Valencia |url=https://www.soyfutbol.com/en/news/obed-vargas-shines-with-assist-in-atletico-madrids-win-over-valencia-20260502-0011.html
 |website=Soy Futbol |date=2026-05-02 |access-date=2026-05-04}}</ref>

==International career==

=== Youth ===
Vargas was eligible to represent both Mexico and the United States at the international level. In March 2020, Vargas was selected to participate in the [[United States boys' national under-15 soccer team|United States national under-15 team]] camp.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Carrick |first1=Buzz |title=Seven Dallas area players named to US U15 team |url=https://3rddegree.net/seven-dallas-area-players-named-to-us-u15-team |access-date=May 10, 2021 |work=3rd Degree |date=March 2, 2020}}</ref> He was called up by the [[United States men's national under-20 soccer team|United States national under-20 team]] in January 2022.<ref name="Times-Veteran" /> On October 8, 2023, Vargas was called up to the [[United States men's national under-23 soccer team|United States national under-23 team]] ahead of friendlies against [[Mexico national under-23 football team|Mexico national under-23]] and [[Japan national under-23 football team|Japan national under-23]] teams.<ref>{{cite web |title=Twenty-three Players Called to U.s. Olympic Men's Soccer Team Training Camp as Preparations for Paris 2024 Kick Off in Phoenix |url=https://www.ussoccer.com/stories/2023/10/23-players-called-to-us-olympic-mens-soccer-team-training-camp |website=ussoccer.com |access-date=October 8, 2023 |date=October 8, 2023}}</ref>

On May 21, 2024, Vargas completed a one-time switch from the United States to Mexico.<ref name="prosoccerwire.usatoday.com" /> On June 20, Vargas was called up to the [[Mexico national under-20 football team|Mexico national under-20 team]] ahead of friendlies against the [[Liga TDP]], [[Cruz Azul|Cruz Azul under-23]] and [[Atlético Morelia]] teams in preparation for the [[2024 CONCACAF U-20 Championship]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://miseleccion.mx/noticias/5543/Convocatoria-de-la-Selecci%C3%B3n-Nacional-de-M%C3%A9xico-Sub-20|title=Convocatoria de la Selección Nacional de México Sub-20|date=June 20, 2024}}</ref> On August 29, Vargas was called up to the [[Mexico national under-23 football team|Mexico national under-23 team]] ahead of two friendlies against the [[Panama national under-23 football team|Panama national under-23 team]] scheduled for September 6 and 10.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://miseleccion.mx/noticias/5631/Convocatoria-Selecci%C3%B3n-Nacional-Sub-23-para-juegos-ante-Panam%C3%A1|title=Convocatoria Selección Nacional Sub-23 para juegos ante Panamá|date=August 29, 2024}}</ref>

In 2025, Vargas was called up by coach [[Eduardo Arce]] to represent Mexico at the [[2025 FIFA U-20 World Cup|FIFA U-20 World Cup]] held in Chile.<ref>{{cite web|title=Convocatoria Oficial de México Sub-20 para el Mundial de Chile|url=https://miseleccion.mx/noticias/6147/Convocatoria-Oficial-de-M%C3%A9xico-Sub-20-para-el-Mundial-de-Chile|website=MiSeleccion.mx|date=September 10, 2025|access-date=September 27, 2025|language=Spanish}}</ref>

===Senior===
Upon completing his [[FIFA eligibility rules|FIFA one-time switch]], in early October 2024, Vargas receives his first call-up to the [[Mexico national football team|senior]] national team for October 11 and 15 for friendly matches against Spanish club [[Valencia CF]] and the [[United States men's national soccer team|United States]] respectively. Vargas is the first [[Alaska]]n to ever play for a national team.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.alaskasnewssource.com/2024/10/10/alaskas-obed-vargas-gets-call-up-mexican-national-team-set-play-us/|title=Alaska's Obed Vargas gets call-up to Mexican National Team, set to play U.S.|date=October 9, 2024|work=[[KTUU-TV|AlaskasNewsSource.com]]|first=Jordan|last=Rodenberger|access-date=October 10, 2024}}</ref> On October 15, Vargas makes his senior Mexico debut entering in the 83rd minute for [[Jesús Alberto Angulo|Jesús Angulo]] in a friendly match against the [[USMNT|United States]], which Mexico won 2–0.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sofascore.com/football/match/mexico-usa/zUbsGVb#id:12749524|title=Mexico–USA|date=October 15, 2024|work=[[Sofascore|Sofascore.com]]|access-date=October 15, 2024}}</ref>

==Personal life==

Vargas is of [[Mexicans|Mexican]] descent and holds dual U.S. and Mexican citizenship. He is set to receive Spanish citizenship during 2026, being eligible due to his mother holding Spanish citizenship.<ref>{{Cite web |date=February 3, 2026 |title=Obed Vargas tendrá pasaporte español; no será jugador extracomunitario en Atlético de Madrid |url=https://www.record.com.mx/historia/obed-vargas-tendra-pasaporte-espanol-no-sera-jugador-extracomunitario-en-atletico-de-madrid-2026020302581923964 |access-date=February 3, 2026 |website=RÉCORD |language=es}}</ref> His father played for the youth academy of [[Atlético Morelia|Monarcas Morelia]]; his younger brother and two sisters also play football.<ref name="Times-Veteran"/><ref>{{cite news |last=Mercado |first=Isabelle |date=n.d. |title=Obed Vargas, a Promising Hispanic Soccer Player |url=https://www.soldemedianochenews.org/obed-vargas-a-promising-hispanic-soccer-player.html |work=[[Sol de Medianoche]] |accessdate=March 12, 2022}}</ref>

